s.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/f8bb0cc0-6e93-11ee-bb8e-7e9b73e93a8f" width="1558"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Amazon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[An image of a Fire TV stick standing in front of a TV. There are candles and tasteful vase.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Amazon Fire TV Stick]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Intel is pushing developers to make AI-enabled PC apps]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果没有充分利用人工智能的应用程序，人工智能驱动的处理器有什么用呢？这似乎是英特尔最近一直在问自己的问题。该公司刚刚宣布了一项新计划，即人工智能 PC 加速计划，旨在帮助开发人员利用英特尔<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/intels-core-ultra-meteor-lake-chips-arrive-on-december-14-153515292.html">即将推出的 Core Ultra 移动芯片</a>创建新的人工智能功能。</p><p>这些处理器将于 12 月 14 日上市，因其是该公司首款包含神经处理单元 (NPU) 的处理器而引人注目。就像 GPU 加速游戏任务一样，NPU 加速 AI 工作负载，例如 Windows 11 视频聊天 Studio Effects 中的背景模糊功能。不过，仅靠 NPU 并不会让人们急于购买新笔记本电脑。英特尔需要的是人们想要人工智能加速的令人信服的理由。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>据英特尔称，进入 AI PC 加速计划，迄今为止，该计划包括 100 多家软件供应商和 300 多个人工智能支持的功能。这些开发者也不只是无名开发者：当前的参与者包括 Audacity、Adobe、BlackMagic、Webex 和 Zoom。作为该计划的一部分，英特尔为开发人员提供了<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Intel;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2d327af4-8b42-4ff1-a409-ae7bf906e9e9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Intel&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5pbnRlbC5jb20vY29udGVudC93d3cvdXMvZW4vZGV2ZWxvcGVyL3Rvb2xzL29wZW52aW5vLXRvb2xraXQvb3ZlcnZpZXcuaHRtbCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzg3ZDBhY2YtMTdjYS00NmU2LTkwMjMtOWNlNDQyNTY1MGE1In0&amp;signature=AQAAAYdRtD6QvNbEQZPPKmuVnnb8wiVmhSPY2t-Fcx4k99K6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.intel.com%2Fcontent%2Fwww%2Fus%2Fen%2Fdeveloper%2Ftools%2Fopenvino-toolkit%2Foverview.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/tools/openvino-toolkit/overview.html">OpenVINO 等人工智能工具包</a>、设计资源和营销帮助。毕竟，这对大多数软件制造商来说都是未知的领域——英特尔的帮助可以帮助他们更快地提供有用的人工智能功能。</p><p> Audacity 产品主管 Martin Keary 在一份声明中表示：“我们 Audacity 很高兴能够与英特尔合作，帮助为广大 AI PC 用户带来强大、开放且最重要的是免费的 AI 工具。” “随着时间的推移，我们期望此类举措能够为音乐家、播客和音响发烧友创造一种新型的创意环境，成为过去 20 年典型的传统音频工具的当之无愧的继承者。”</p><p>英特尔客户端技术和性能营销高级总监 Robert Hallock 告诉 Engadget，这并不是英特尔第一次尝试推动开发人员构建新的人工智能功能。它针对服务器和数据中心运行了类似的计划，从而产生了<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Intel;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2d327af4-8b42-4ff1-a409-ae7bf906e9e9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Intel&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5pbnRlbC5jb20vY29udGVudC93d3cvdXMvZW4vaW50ZXJuZXQtb2YtdGhpbmdzL2FpLWluLXByb2R1Y3Rpb24vcGFydG5lcnMtc29sdXRpb25zLWNhdGFsb2cuaHRtbCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzg3ZDBhY2YtMTdjYS00NmU2LTkwMjMtOWNlNDQyNTY1MGE1In0&amp;signature=AQAAAYlGgW6B6i9HOwyPgd3D8nleddX1rcYAl34UanAamXXn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.intel.com%2Fcontent%2Fwww%2Fus%2Fen%2Finternet-of-things%2Fai-in-production%2Fpartners-solutions-catalog.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/internet-of-things/ai-in-production/partners-solutions-catalog.html">大约 1,000 个支持人工智能的软件示例</a>。开发人员将能够在线注册 AI PC 加速计划，然后英特尔将确定其资格以及他们所需的资源。</p><p> Hallock 指出，英特尔人工智能推动的成果也不仅限于该公司的 NPU，它们还应该在 AMD 和英特尔的人工智能硬件上运行，而无需太多额外的努力。展望未来，他预计 NPU 将成为所有 PC 处理器中的通用组件，使它们成为开发人员更值得依赖的东西。开发人员仍会针对延迟敏感的工作使用 CPU，而游戏和 3D 渲染将直接使用 GPU 功能。但 NPU 将成为长时间运行、耗电密集型人工智能任务的首选解决方案，因为它比 GPU 和 CPU 效率更高。</p><p> “在追求每瓦性能的过程中，拥有第三个加速器会带来很大的不同，”哈洛克说。 “它可以延长电池寿命，允许 GPU 卸载。这是主要优势之一。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/intel-ai-pc-acceleration-program-core-ultra-150054881.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/intel-ai-pc-acceleration-program-core-ultra-150054881.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 787d0acf-17ca-46e6-9023-9ce4425650a5</guid><dc:creator>德文德拉·哈达瓦尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 15:00:54 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1697689339</ingested><modified> 2023-10-19T04:22:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Devindra Hardawar]]></category><media:content height="3327" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3a01c220-2d88-11ee-b37f-06de1ca1df15" width="5000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3327" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3a01c220-2d88-11ee-b37f-06de1ca1df15" width="5000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[POLAND - 2023/07/19: In this photo illustration an Intel logo is displayed on a smartphone with Artificial Intelligence (AI) symbols in the background. (Photo Illustration by Omar Marques/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[In this photo illustration an Intel logo is displayed on a...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Discord’s latest teen safety blitz starts with content filters and automated warnings]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Discord 正在引入新的保护措施来保护年轻用户。周四，该公司<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://discord.com/blog/best-place-to-hang-out-with-friends" data-original-link="https://discord.com/blog/best-place-to-hang-out-with-friends"><ins>宣布推出青少年安全辅助系统</ins></a>。随着本周的首次推出，该计划包含两个功能：自动警报和内容过滤器。</p><p>展望未来，当以前从未与青少年聊天的用户发送直接消息时，如果平台的自动化系统怀疑青少年的安全可能面临风险，Discord 将显示安全警报。该提示将促使年轻人重新考虑是否要回复该消息，并向他们指出应用程序的阻止功能和相关的安全提示。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>默认情况下，Discord 现在还会自动模糊青少年朋友的潜在敏感图像，并删除陌生人的敏感内容。年轻人可以通过 Discord 设置菜单中的选项禁用该功能。与此同时，如果成年人想要额外的保护，他们可以自己启用过滤器。</p><p>青少年安全辅助系统的推出正值 Discord 为限制儿童性虐待材料 (CSAM) 的传播和保护青少年用户免受成人掠夺而做出的努力受到越来越多的审查之际。 6 月， <em>NBC 新闻</em><a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/discord-still-has-a-child-safety-issue-085304790.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/discord-still-has-a-child-safety-issue-085304790.html"><ins>发现了 6 年间发生的 35 起案件</ins></a>，其中成年人涉嫌利用该平台绑架、诱骗或性侵犯未成年人。该媒体还发现了 165 起案件，当局正在起诉成年人通过 Discord 分享 CSAM 或涉嫌利用该平台勒索年轻用户发送自己的色情图片。</p><p>该报告发布后，Discord <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/discord-bans-teen-dating-servers-and-the-sharing-of-ai-generated-csam-071626058.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/discord-bans-teen-dating-servers-and-the-sharing-of-ai-generated-csam-071626058.html"><ins>禁止青少年约会服务器</ins></a>，并更改其安全政策以禁止共享人工智能生成的 CSAM。它还宣布了新规则，明确禁止任何其他类型的使儿童色情的文本或媒体内容。与此同时，该公司<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/new-family-center-tool-gives-parents-better-insight-into-their-teens-discord-usage-150014579.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/new-family-center-tool-gives-parents-better-insight-into-their-teens-discord-usage-150014579.html"><ins>推出了 Family Center</ins></a> ，这是一个供父母和监护人跟踪青少年在 Discord 上做什么的仪表板。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/14c4d120-6e86-11ee-97fe-eec9213b0ac4" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/14c4d120-6e86-11ee-97fe-eec9213b0ac4" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Discord 青少年安全工具" data-uuid="bf5a1576-cde6-386b-bb73-0aea123685ec"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">不和谐</div></figure><p>“青少年仍在了解自己以及在线意味着什么，我们新的安全功能植根于为他们在平台上提供代理，为他们提供在安全且适合年龄的在线学习和成长的方法Discord 高级政策总监萨凡纳·巴达里奇 (Savannah Badalich) 表示。 “这些最新功能是多年来不断发展和提高 Discord 安全性努力的一部分。”</p><p>与此同时，Discord 正在为违反其政策的人引入新的警告系统。除了涉及最“极端”违规的事件外，该公司正在摆脱永久禁令。它这样做的信念是，只要有机会和适当的指导，大多数用户都会选择成为更好的在线公民。</p><p>实际上，当用户违反一项或多项 Discord 政策时，系统会通知用户，并详细说明对其帐户的限制。它还将链接到公司的<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:5;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://discord.com/terms/" data-original-link="https://discord.com/terms/"><ins>服务条款</ins></a>、 <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:6;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://discord.com/guidelines" data-original-link="https://discord.com/guidelines"><ins>社区准则</ins></a>和上诉机制。设置菜单中的新“帐户信誉”选项卡将允许用户查看所有当前和过去的政策违规行为。</p><p> Badalich 告诉 Engadget：“我们认为我们已经建立了最细致、最相称的报告系统。”他补充说，该公司希望其他平台能够从 Discord 所创建的内容中获得灵感，以促进他们自己的执法工作。 “我们相信人们，尤其是青少年，有成长的能力。”</p><p>另外，Discord 宣布了一系列新功能和增强功能，预计将在不久的将来或将来推出。首先，Discord 上个月开始对<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:7;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/discord-nitro-basic-activities-150041805.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/discord-nitro-basic-activities-150041805.html"><ins>Nitro 订阅者</ins></a>进行测试，该平台的应用内商店很快将向所有用户开放。该市场提供人们可以用来装饰自己的头像和个人资料的数字物品。 Discord 将为 Nitro 会员提供商店折扣，作为注册新福利的一部分。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/c553caa0-6e86-11ee-bbfb-b01e8d086a33" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/c553caa0-6e86-11ee-bbfb-b01e8d086a33" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Discord 青少年安全更新" data-uuid="3b32479a-261c-3862-a106-856fa2587180"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">不和谐</div></figure><p>本周，该公司还将开始推出一项名为<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:8;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://discord.com/blog/meme-up-some-fun-with-remix" data-original-link="https://discord.com/blog/meme-up-some-fun-with-remix"><ins>Remix 的</ins></a>功能。它允许用户直接在 Discord 的移动应用程序中编辑图像并与他们的朋友和服务器共享。该公司去年花了大部分时间改进其 Android 和 iOS 客户端。最近的一项更新改进了两个平台上的应用程序启动时间。 Discord 表示，在不久的将来，人们可以期待新的“午夜”黑暗模式，该公司声称可以减少配备 OLED 屏幕的设备的电池消耗、功能更多的通知选项卡以及设置菜单的新搜索功能，以便更轻松地找到确切的内容您想要调整的选项。</p><p>最后但并非最不重要的一点是，该公司表示，继几周前在美国开始推出<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:9;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/9359445233303-Premium-App-Subscriptions-FAQ" data-original-link="https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/9359445233303-Premium-App-Subscriptions-FAQ"><ins>高级应用程序订阅</ins></a>后，它将开始向英国和欧洲符合条件的开发者推出高级应用程序订阅。关于第三方应用程序、机器人和插件的问题，该公司表示正在探索如何让这些内容在 Discord 的几乎每个部分都可以访问。它没有提供有关这项工作的一些细节，但表示目标是允许人们访问他们最喜欢的应用程序和机器人，而这些体验不会仅限于选定的服务器。</p><p> “我们正在尝试一些不同的事情，但目标是让开发人员向更多人提供他们正在构建的出色体验。对于用户来说，我们不希望他们无法轻松获得这些定制体验。”Discord 产品营销总监 Cherry Park 告诉 Engadget。 “就我们的架构和构建方式而言，有几种解决方案。有些更容易，有些更困难，你将在接下来的几个季度看到我们对其中一些进行实验。”</p><p> Discord 承诺在不久的将来分享更多有关应用程序可移植性方面的努力。与此同时，Nitro 订阅者将有机会在新功能向公众开放之前对其进行测试。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/discords-latest-teen-safety-blitz-starts-with-content-filters-and-automated-warnings-150031569.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/discords-latest-teen-safety-blitz-starts-with-content-filters-and-automated-warnings-150031569.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 040952af-fada-47c8-87d1-6a9bd535e558</guid><dc:creator>伊戈尔·博尼法西奇</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 15:00:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1697723859</ingested><modified> 2023-10-19T13:57:47+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Igor Bonifacic]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/eaa9db10-6e85-11ee-a6ff-31040c73d76d" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/eaa9db10-6e85-11ee-a6ff-31040c73d76d" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Discord]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Discord teen safety updates]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Discord teen safety updates]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[OnePlus Open review: A thinner and more affordable flagship foldable]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>三星是第一家制造出真正的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-foldable-phones-160030013.html">可折叠手机的</a>制造商，但它有点自满了。现在，OnePlus 发布了首款配备柔性屏幕的手机，并且已经与<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/galaxy-z-fold-5-review-five-years-in-samsung-is-treading-water-140002461.html">Galaxy Z Fold 5</a>展开了竞争。 Open 不仅内部和外部的显示屏更大，而且更薄、更轻。也就是说，只要不算其庞大的摄像头模块。凭借其 Open Canvas 软件，OnePlus 正在采用一种新颖的多任务处理方法，使应用程序之间的切换变得超级快速且轻松。</p><p>但也许 Open 所做的最令人印象深刻的事情是对大型精美可折叠手机的价格施加压力，因为它的起价为 1,700 美元，比 Z Fold 5 和<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-fold-review-the-challenger-that-samsung-needs-specs-price-170003458.html">谷歌 Pixel Fold</a>便宜 100 美元 - 而且这还是在你考虑 OnePlus 的交易之前以旧换新<em>任何</em>手机还可再优惠 200 美元。今年我们已经看到谷歌发布了首款可折叠手机，OnePlus Open 的到来为该类别增添了更多的兴奋点。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="db642e9f6db8418b8de195e8a6c2a945"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7e4ueoeQgEA?si=t9A215LiCb0aL_oX" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p><core-commerce id="3567ed5402464ac783de1c383d5cb0a4" data-type="product-list"></p><h2>显示屏：超亮</h2><p>与三星 Galaxy Z Fold 系列类似，OnePlus Open 配备两个显示屏：一个 6.3 英寸的外部屏幕和一个内部的 7.8 英寸柔性面板。这两个面板都比 Z Fold 5 上的面板稍大，同时还具有 120Hz 刷新率。但 OnePlus 真正推动的是亮度，正常使用时亮度可达 1,400 尼特左右，在某些情况下（例如在户外观看 HDR 内容时）可达令人惊叹的 2,800 尼特。再说一次，这适用于两个显示器。然而，这些数字是如此之高，它超出了我的色度计，所以我无法完全验证 OnePlus 的说法。无论如何，亮度从来都不是问题。</p><h2>设计：每一克都很重要</h2><p>OnePlus并没有过多地模仿三星的模板，而是坚持向内折叠的设计。然而，公司确实试图削减每一克或每一毫米的重量。黑色型号采用纯素皮革背面，重量仅为 239 克，仅比<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-iphone-14-pro-max-review-dynamic-island-useful-always-on-display-battery-life-camera-test-sample-pictures-130020449.html">iPhone 14 Pro Max</a>轻一克。与此同时，我们的翡翠黄昏评测设备采用玻璃背板，重量仅为 245 克。</p><p> Open 的外观也非常时尚，厚度仅为 11.7 毫米。这比 Pixel Fold（12.1 毫米）还要薄。也就是说，除非考虑到其巨大的摄像头模块，这使得手机的真实厚度达到 18 毫米左右。 Open 还拥有更宽的外部显示屏，这使得打字更加流畅，而且不会增加太多体积。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/8dae5380-6e82-11ee-b77f-9156839f9cfd" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/8dae5380-6e82-11ee-b77f-9156839f9cfd" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="OnePlus Open 的厚度为 11.7 毫米，甚至比 Google Pixel Fold（12.1 毫米）还要薄，只要你不计算其巨大的摄像头凸起。" data-uuid="216be14a-ff77-330d-a8b8-3a6b4fb4426d"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>当然，可折叠设备最受关注的一些领域是其铰链和折痕。值得庆幸的是，OnePlus 在这两方面都做得很好。主显示屏中间有一条微弱的凹槽，但很微妙。只有从锐角观察或真正去寻找它时，您才会注意到它。</p><p>铰链也非常光滑，与竞争对手不同，它有一点弹簧加载的作用。因此，在某一点之后，它就会完全打开。这是 Pixel Fold 带来的一个不错的变化，无论你做什么，它似乎总是停在 179 度。我欣赏的另一个细节是，打开关闭时齐平，因此您不必担心钥匙或其他小物体进入内部。不幸的是，您只能获得 IPX4 防水等级，远远低于 Pixel Fold 和 Z Fold 5 的 IP68 等级。</p><h2>性能：移动多任务处理变得简单</h2><p>OnePlus Open 采用 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 芯片，其性能与 Galaxy Z Fold 5 非常相似。由于时钟速度稍高，三星手机在 Geekbench 6 等测试中确实领先 5% 到 10%。但在日常使用过程中，优势基本感觉不出来。但 OnePlus 确实拥有 16GB 内存（Z Fold 为 12GB）以及 512GB 基本存储——这是三星和谷歌的两倍。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/c02a5e30-6e82-11ee-9697-e3ffe7245326" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/c02a5e30-6e82-11ee-9697-e3ffe7245326" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="OnePlus 的 Open Canvas 软件可让您通过 UI 轻松执行多项任务，让应用程序像卡片一样滑入和滑出视图。" data-uuid="e3d458ad-d68b-321c-b2f6-3b340bb6718c"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>然而，我最喜欢 Open 的一点是它处理多任务的方式。显然，您可以做一些事情，例如在分屏中打开两个应用程序。但如果您想要更多，OnePlus 的 Open Canvas 软件可以一次打开三个应用程序，并通过小选项卡让您只需轻按一下即可移动内容。就像每个应用程序都是一张小卡片，可以根据您的需要滑入和滑出视图，而且效果出奇地好。它比向上滑动并按住打开最近的应用程序要快得多，但不会增加太多混乱。作为对三星和谷歌任务栏的调整，OnePlus 为最近的文件添加了专用图标，因此可以非常轻松地将文档或照片拖放到电子邮件或消息中。</p><p>也就是说，作为一个喜欢旧版本 Oxygen OS 的人，我觉得 OnePlus 的 UI 当前设计（在该公司与 Oppo 合并后）看起来有点廉价。除了快速设置之外，几乎每个按钮都是某种圆角矩形，虽然它很实用，但也有点无聊。</p><h2>相机：哈苏的一大进步</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/133f22e0-6e83-11ee-bfd7-57b8520036ff" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/133f22e0-6e83-11ee-bfd7-57b8520036ff" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="OnePlus Open 配备三个后置摄像头，包括带有大型 1/1.43 英寸传感器的 48 MP 主摄像头、64 MP 长焦摄像头和还可以拍摄微距照片的 48 MP 超广角摄像头。" data-uuid="d306465d-0ab9-383a-8e72-09b15ad7cd79"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p> Ever since OnePlus partnered with Hasselblad to upgrade its cameras, the modules on the backs of its phones have gotten bigger and bigger. And while it&#39;s a bit of an eyesore, the Open&#39;s huge camera bump isn&#39;t without reason as it holds a large 1/1.43-inch 64-MP LYTIA T808 main sensor from Sony with a new pixel architecture designed to increase the amount of light it can capture for even better nighttime photos. OnePlus claims it delivers the best image quality on any foldable available today and, while I won&#39;t go quite that far, its pics are relatively close to what you can capture with a Pixel Fold. Photos are sharp and detailed, the one shortcoming is that OnePlus&#39; low-light processing isn&#39;t quite as good as Google&#39;s Night Sight. But compared to the Z Fold 5, the Open&#39;s pics often had better dynamic range and less exaggerated sharpening.</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="3f7fab9c-1713-479f-833d-cee834d4ec53"/><p> You also get a 48-MP ultra-wide cam that can also shoot macros, and a 64-MP telephoto with a 3x optical zoom that goes up to a 6x lossless magnification. Once again, while that 3x zoom is every bit a match for the Z Fold 5&#39;s 3x telephoto cam, it&#39;s 6x lossless just isn&#39;t quite as sharp as the 5x optical lens on the Pixel Fold. But that&#39;s not a big surprise because there still isn&#39;t a true replacement for high-quality glass.</p><h2> Battery life: Great longevity but no wireless charging?!</h2><p> OnePlus has always had somewhat spotty support for wireless charging. Its first phone to have it was the <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/one-plus-8-pro-review-5g-120-hz-quad-camera-155534134.html">OnePlus 8 Pro</a> in 2020, which was years after its competitors got on board. That support continued on the OnePlus 9, <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-9-pro-review-hasselblad-cameras-price-performance-150053710.html">OnePlus 9 Pro</a> , and the <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/one-plus-10-pro-review-specs-price-camera-comparison-143032415-143032439.html">OnePlus 10 Pro</a> . But then OnePlus dropped wireless charging for the <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/one-plus-10-t-review-speed-above-all-specs-price-availability-153054303.html">10T</a> and the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-11-review-price-release-date-cameras-150015371.html">11</a> , and unfortunately, we don&#39;t get it here on the Open either. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/6b650de0-6e83-11ee-9ff5-bfa31cd52794" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/6b650de0-6e83-11ee-9ff5-bfa31cd52794" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="While the Open features speedy 67-watt wired charging, sadly it doesn&#39;t support any form of wireless charging." data-uuid="401e0ee0-e5eb-3a8b-b813-dae5f475f244"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p> The lack of wireless charging on any $1,000 phone is pretty disappointing, let alone a brand new flagship foldable. My suspicion is that OnePlus didn&#39;t include it because charging coils would have added one or two millimeters in thickness, which would have detracted from the phone&#39;s design. And if that&#39;s true, that&#39;s a pretty weak justification.</p><p> On the bright side, wired charging is significantly faster than its competition at 67 watts. And it&#39;s even faster in Europe at 80 watts due to their 240-volt power standard. However, because of OnePlus&#39; proprietary charging system, you only get those speeds when you use the included brick, so if you switch to a third-party adapter, speeds drop in half to around 30 watts.</p><p> Thankfully battery life is great. With its exterior display, the Open lasted 25 and a half hours on our video rundown test, which is an hour and a half better than the Z Fold 5. And with its main display, it lasted just over 19 hours, which is also quite respectable.</p><h2> Pricing: An almost unbelievable discount </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/2a1f8030-6e84-11ee-beec-2df86672ae08" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/2a1f8030-6e84-11ee-beec-2df86672ae08" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="The Open&#39;s 6.3-inch exterior display doesn&#39;t sound like a big increase over the Z Fold 5&#39;s 6.2-inch Cover Screen, but that tiny bit of added width makes a big difference in overall usability." data-uuid="44921784-464e-3d9a-b23b-664bb094069e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p> When it comes to pricing, big foldables like this have always been pretty expensive, though at $1,700, the Open costs $100 less than both the Z Fold 5 and the Pixel Fold. But to sweeten the pot even further, OnePlus has an enticing deal that will knock another $200 off the price with the trade-in of any phone. Typically there are some limits or restrictions to promos like this, so I had to confirm the details with OnePlus. But the company really does mean any device, regardless of how old it is or what condition it&#39;s in. That means you can finally get rid of the Nokia brick that&#39;s been living in a drawer for the last 10 or 15 years and get some value out of it. And if you do, you&#39;re looking at an effective price of $1,500, which still ain&#39;t cheap, but it is significantly lower than the competition. The caveat is that this discount is only available directly through OnePlus.</p><h2> Wrap-up</h2><p> When I first heard OnePlus was making a foldable phone, I wasn&#39;t sure what their goal was. The company hasn&#39;t been in the business of making flagship killers for a while. But with the Open, OnePlus has crammed some rather impressive hardware into a device with a novel approach to multitasking. The Open&#39;s cameras are as good if not slightly better than what you get on a Z Fold 5, and it has bigger screens too. Honestly, there are a lot of things about the Open&#39;s design that I wish we were getting from Samsung, as opposed to the three years of minor refinements we&#39;ve seen following the release of the Z Fold 3. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/9778edc0-6e83-11ee-bcfa-733fde2ecc29" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/9778edc0-6e83-11ee-bcfa-733fde2ecc29" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Along with a cable and OnePlus&#39; proprietary charging brick, the Open also comes with an included case which is a nice bit of added value." data-uuid="fa020842-7e97-37fb-b8dc-57dd909cc82b"><figcaption> Along with a cable and OnePlus&#39; proprietary charging brick, the Open also comes with an included case which is a nice bit of added value.</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p> It&#39;s also important to note that the Open has an alter ego, because depending on where you live, this thing will also be known as the Oppo Find N3. The two phones are essentially the same device just with <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.androidpolice.com/oppo-find-n3-first-real-world-images/">different branding.</a> That said, the Open will still get four years of Android updates and five years of security patches along with support for all the major US carriers. But unlike Google and Samsung&#39;s offerings, the Open will only be available through online retailers and because OnePlus doesn&#39;t have any local US retail partners, the only way to get the Open serviced is to send it in. That&#39;s a bit of concern as pretty much every foldable phone tends to have an issue with its built-in screen protector bubbling after about a year. So even though OnePlus offers free shipping for repairs under warranty, no one wants to be without their phone for a week or more while it&#39;s in the shop.</p><p> Still, I&#39;m impressed with what OnePlus is bringing out the gate.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-open-review-a-thinner-and-more-affordable-flagship-foldable-specs-price-150031633.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-open-review-a-thinner-and-more-affordable-flagship-foldable-specs-price-150031633.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6beda52c-9c66-4710-beda-1ba2588a8242</guid><dc:creator>萨姆·卢瑟福</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 15:00:29 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1697727968</ingested><modified> 2023-10-19T15:06:15+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/4a634e50-6e82-11ee-bb77-a849c0bd0ceb" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/4a634e50-6e82-11ee-bb77-a849c0bd0ceb" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Despite being OnePlus' first foldable phone, the Open features slim, lightweight design with super bright screens and a novel approach to multitasking.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The OnePlus Open]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Alienware's latest gaming laptop is the first to feature AMD's Radeon RX 7900M GPU]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Alienware just announced a refresh to the <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alienwares-refreshed-m-17-r-5-gaming-laptop-is-getting-a-super-fast-480-hz-display-130024526.html">popular m17 R5 gaming laptop.</a> The m17 was already a stellar example of an AMD Advantage system and the m18 kicks this up a notch or two. The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dell;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b1bb23c9-a2d4-4e4e-bfac-7a560ebe7641&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dell&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5kZWxsLmNvbS9lbi11cy9zaG9wL2RlbGwtbGFwdG9wcy9zci9sYXB0b3BzL2FsaWVud2FyZS1sYXB0b3BzLzE4LWluY2g_YXBwbGllZFJlZmluZW1lbnRzPTQxNDcwLDM3NjMzLDM3NjQ3IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIzNDkzZjY2OC1jNWFiLTQ2MWQtOWVhNS1jZDQ1Mjc0M2JhNjIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAT6eFZIwpi0umZmFS0CdyrnGMo5mF4p3hTg09K3OI-HA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dell.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fdell-laptops%2Fsr%2Flaptops%2Falienware-laptops%2F18-inch%3FappliedRefinements%3D41470%2C37633%2C37647" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.dell.com/en-us/shop/dell-laptops/sr/laptops/alienware-laptops/18-inch?appliedRefinements=41470,37633,37647">Alienware m18</a> goes all-in with AMD integration, with the company boasting that its the “most powerful 18-inch AMD Advantage laptop” ever made.</p><p> The term AMD Advantage is marketing speak for a computer that&#39;s built from the ground up for gaming via various AMD chipsets and technologies. To that end, the m18 is the first computer to feature the all-new AMD Radeon RX 7900M laptop graphics chip. These laptops also come equipped with the well-regarded <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amds-ryzen-7000-mobile-cpus-16-core-033046361.html">AMD Ryzen 7945HX CPU.</a> So, yeah, this thing&#39;s a beast, with Alienware calling it a “performance juggernaut.”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> The Radeon RX 7900M has been engineered to deliver “desktop-class” visuals even when playing power-hungry AAA titles. The GPU is filled with techy features, like second-gen raytracing accelerators, 16GB of GDDR6 VRAM and other “advanced capabilities to push the limits of gaming and content creation on the go.”</p><p> The Ryzen 9 7945 CPU helps everything move along thanks to 16 performance cores, 32 processing threads and AMD&#39;s proprietary Zen 4 chiplet technology. The CPU was manufactured using the new 5nm design, the first for gaming laptops, which promises better power efficiency and faster performance.</p><p> These laptops ship with AMD&#39;s Adrenaline Edition software suite, so you can access the SmartShift tool to shift power between the GPU and CPU in real-time to boost performance. Additionally, the company&#39;s proprietary SmartAccess graphics tech automatically prioritizes game performance and reduced latency when using FreeSync. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/75b43040-62e5-11ee-bdb7-c3cad2914647" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/75b43040-62e5-11ee-bdb7-c3cad2914647" style="height:2400px;width:2400px;" alt="A laptop computer." data-uuid="0dc89b42-0c70-3922-9c6c-eea15ac07dd4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Alienware</div></figure><p> Laptops are more than just numbers on a spreadsheet, however, and the m18 has some other perks worth mentioning. These computers come equipped with Alienware&#39;s Cryo-tech thermal regulation technology. This thermal interface material extends to both the CPU and GPU, with an expanded vapor chamber covering each component, helping to dissipate heat across the entire system. Four thin fans finish this process by pulling heated air through eight heat pipes and out via five vents.</p><p> You also get an 18-inch display panel equipped with both Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos, with a 16:10 aspect ratio, QHD+ resolution and a maximum refresh rate of 165Hz. You can overclock this refresh rate all the way to 480Hz at the expense of resolution for competitive gaming scenarios. An FHD webcam and an IR camera for facial recognition are also on board.</p><p> As for RAM and storage, there&#39;s user-replaceable dual-channel DDR5 memory and you can shop options with up to three M.2 SSDs for a combined total of 8.5TB of storage. The laptop boasts some aesthetic flourishes, like an aluminum lid and bottom cover, an aluminum die-cast inner frame and an embossed &quot;18&quot; on the exterior. The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dell;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b1bb23c9-a2d4-4e4e-bfac-7a560ebe7641&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dell&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5kZWxsLmNvbS9lbi11cy9zaG9wL2RlbGwtbGFwdG9wcy9zci9sYXB0b3BzL2FsaWVud2FyZS1sYXB0b3BzLzE4LWluY2g_YXBwbGllZFJlZmluZW1lbnRzPTQxNDcwLDM3NjMzLDM3NjQ3IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIzNDkzZjY2OC1jNWFiLTQ2MWQtOWVhNS1jZDQ1Mjc0M2JhNjIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAT6eFZIwpi0umZmFS0CdyrnGMo5mF4p3hTg09K3OI-HA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dell.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fdell-laptops%2Fsr%2Flaptops%2Falienware-laptops%2F18-inch%3FappliedRefinements%3D41470%2C37633%2C37647" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.dell.com/en-us/shop/dell-laptops/sr/laptops/alienware-laptops/18-inch?appliedRefinements=41470,37633,37647">m18 is available today</a> with a starting price of $2,800. </p><p><core-commerce id="7383af6548cb40909f3b6d1c73d401da" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/alienwares-latest-gaming-laptop-is-the-first-to-feature-amds-radeon-rx-7900m-gpu-130033731.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/alienwares-latest-gaming-laptop-is-the-first-to-feature-amds-radeon-rx-7900m-gpu-130033731.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3493f668-c5ab-461d-9ea5-cd452743ba62</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 13:00:33 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1697723189</ingested><modified> 2023-10-19T13:46:34+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="6006" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/1bc45ab0-62e5-11ee-9b7f-c628dd5bfc77" width="8012"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="6006" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/1bc45ab0-62e5-11ee-9b7f-c628dd5bfc77" width="8012"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Alienware]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A laptop on a table.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Alienware m18]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[AMD's Radeon RX 7900M is its most powerful mobile GPU yet]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> AMD has unveiled the Radeon RX 7900M mobile GPU built around its <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amd-rdna-3-laptops-radeon-rx-7000-033006886.html">RDNA 3 architecture</a> , its fastest mobile gaming chip to date and &quot;first-even chiplet laptop graphics.&quot; The company has positioned the new chips for high FPS 1440p (QHD) gaming rather than 4K as a way to boost regular laptop gaming. AMD is also touting its FSR 3 (FidelityFX Super Resolution) upscaling tech that&#39;s similar to NVIDIA&#39;s DLSS 3, promising a large boost in frame rates for games like <em>Starfield</em> and <em>Forspoken</em> .</p><p> As a flagship chip, the RX 7900M comes with 72 compute units (compared to <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amd-rdna-3-laptops-radeon-rx-7000-033006886.html">32 for the RX 7700S</a> ) and features 16GB of GDDR6 RAM, while consuming up to 180 watts — well beyond the 110 watt TDP of NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 4080 mobile chip. AMD claims it can outperform the latter by 7 percent on average in terms of frame rates, while offering an additional 4GB of GDDR6 RAM. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/37543030-6e74-11ee-bff1-73d498770b54" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/37543030-6e74-11ee-bff1-73d498770b54" style="height:1204px;width:2238px;" alt="AMD&#39;s Radeon RX7900M is its most powerful mobile GPU yet" data-uuid="802eab9b-8d4b-308e-aad5-a6669c3b94f0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> AMD</div></figure><p> In one example, AMD claimed it could beat a laptop with an RTX 4080 mobile chip by 27 percent on <em>Starfield</em> with a 62 fps frame rate (FSR 2, Ultra 1440p). In another, it said that Forspoken could run at 201 fps with FSR 3 turned on, compared to 63 fps with the setting disabled. It also listed higher frame rates for a number of rasterized games, though it was beaten by a majority ray-traced games run on NVIDIA RTX 4080 GPU-equipped laptops. This is an issue we <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amd-radeon-7900-xtx-xt-review-better-4k-gaming-140002305.html">flagged</a> after reviewing the Radeon RX 7900 XTX and 7900 XT desktop processors last year.</p><p> Along with the mobile GPU, AMD announced a partnership with Alienware, integrating its RX 7900M and Ryzen 9 7945HX processor into the m18 laptop. Along with those chips, that model comes with an 18-inch QHD+ (2,560 x 1,600) display, up to 64GB of RAM, 8.5GB of storage max, and more. That model, along with the RX 7900M, is set to arrive in Q4 2023, when we can hopefully put AMD&#39;s claims to the test.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/amds-radeon-rx-7900m-is-its-most-powerful-mobile-gpu-yet-130013737.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amds-radeon-rx-7900m-is-its-most-powerful-mobile-gpu-yet-130013737.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 060fe791-56a9-4085-96c4-055b55be3c39</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 13:00:13 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1697716740</ingested><modified> 2023-10-19T11:59:03+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="838" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/c5664000-6e6c-11ee-a7df-efc0b6050b2e" width="1378"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA